This paper deals with privacy concerns in Web service recommendation, which is a topic related to security and privacy (cs.CR). It also involves personalized QoS prediction, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed framework involves data obfuscation techniques, which is a topic related to data management and privacy (cs.DB). The development of privacy-preserving QoS prediction approaches also involves machine learning techniques, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed approaches involves a publicly-available QoS dataset, which is a topic related to systems and networking (cs.SI).
